snippet.textDisplay:
Hey man, love the videos! I have a question on the time it takes you to complete a detail. I understand some cars might need more attention than others, much like the one in this video, but I was wondering how you communicate to your customer that it will take "X" amount of hours. For most people, their cars/ trucks are their daily drivers, and when someone brings me their car to get detailed I feel this pressure to have it done within a reasonable amount of time (usually 5-6 hours). Due to this pressure, I tend to miss small things or not take as much time on areas that really need it. I love detailing, I just hate not turning in my best work to a customer that needs it. I know I can produce quality details I just feel like I lack time.


I apologize for such a long comment, I should've just emailed you lol. I appreciate any response you can give me.
